!=========================== LoKiCore v3r0 2007-06-11 ======================
! 2007-06-10 - Vanya BELYAEV

 - many changes: preparation for the next major LoKi release.
 - also make few important fixes:
     
     1) split verrylarge files into mor emanageable pieces 
     2) make possible to reuse full LoKi functionality for 
        functions with two arguments (needed for HLT purposes) using nice trick 
        "twho is just the special case of one"
     3) Make LoKi much more flexible with respect to argument types, 
        up to now it was too "pointer-oriented".

  New files:
  
  1) LoKi/BiFunctions.h
     the base for 2-argument functions: "tho is just the special case of one"
  2) LoKi/Field.h
     simple class which allows the uniform treatment of references and pointers
  3) LoKi/Holder.h
     the major class for "twho as the special case of one" trick
  4) LoKi/Primitives.h
     collection of primitive function (former part of LoKi/Functions.h)
  5) LoKi/Reference.h
     important class to consider references as object 
  6) LoKi/same.h
     fixes for non-pointer argument 
  7) LoKi/valid.h
     fixes for non-pointer argument 

