! 2006-02-22 - Vanya BELYAEV
 - LoKi/Keeper.h
   LoKi/UniqueKeeper.h
   two new templated container adapters, 
   which are useful to keep valid 
   pointer "const OBJECT*"
   The containers implements rudimentaty STL interface 
   which is simultaneously "vector"-like and "set"-like
   By construction, the containers hold *ONLY* valid objects.
   The difference: UniqueKeeper<OBBJECT> contains no duplicates 
   (it is based on std::set), while Keeper<OBJECT> may contains 
   duplicates. From technicla point of view UniqueKeeper is always 
   sorted, thats why std::binary_search could be efficiently  
   applied  


